  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Rivers of Life&quot; - Food Security and Community Development in Rio Coco, North Atlantic Autonomous Region (RAAN)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Main project activities are: development and implementation of food security and nutrition plans, provision of ongoing technical assistance for food production, processing and marketing; workshops for farming techniques and innovative technology; dissemination of low-cost water-catchment systems, community meetings for planning, joint reflection and participatory evaluation; indigenous-to-indigenous exchanges among communities; and joint marketing activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&#x2019;s goal is to promote experimentation and adoption of innovative farming concepts and techniques and improve traditional ones to achieve sustainable improvements in the food and nutritional security situation of indigenous families living in extreme poverty in Nicaragua&#x2019;s North Atlantic Autonomous Region (RAAN), one of Central America&#x2019;s areas most vulnerable to natural disasters. Beneficiary families learn and adopt new farming techniques and skills and improve traditional ones so as to allow them to gradually diversify their farms, secure production of enough nutritious food for their families for the entire year and generate some surplus to sale locally.</narrative>
  </description>
